OL,6,FAs well as arguing that climate change
OL,7,Fwas "more serious even than
OL,8,Fterrorism", he also sharply criticised
OL,9,Fthe Bush administration over its
OL,10,Ffailure to ratify the international
OL,11,FKyoto Protocol and its unwillingness
OL,12,Fto countenance any remedial action.
OL,14,FFollowing its publication, Britain's
OL,15,Fcharge d'affaires in Washington, Tony
OL,16,FBrenton, informed No 10 that he had
OL,17,Fbeen tackled by "a rather worked up"
OL,18,FJim Connaughton, a senior White House
OL,19,Fadviser on the environment, demanding
OL,20,Fan explanation.
OL,26,@oD@EOUpD@JO]yD@QOUyD@dO]
