OL,3,CUS fury at chief scientist's 'dig' at
OL,4,CGeorge Bush's 'war on terror'
OL,6,F"For good measure, he added that the
OL,7,Farticle misrepresented US policy and
OL,8,Fthat David might usefully reread the
OL,9,Fpresident's public utterances on
OL,10,Fclimate change".
OL,12,FMr Brenton said that while he doubted
OL,13,Fthe outrage was a intense as Mr
OL,14,FConnaughton was suggesting, the
OL,15,Fcomparison with the terrorist threat
OL,16,Fhad been "bound to go down badly" and
OL,17,Fthat Sir David should be braced for
OL,18,F"some pushback" when he visited
OL,19,FWashington later that year.
